<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-06-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1746" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1746">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.0145/7.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 168.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I acknowledge the receipt of your
                            despatch No. 558, of May 16, in further reference to the proposal of the
                            Russian Government to secure the passage through the Duma of a law
                            extending to twelve miles from low-water mark the area of the
                            territorial waters which shall be supervised by the Russian customs
                            authorities.</p>
                        <p>You are requested to keep the Department advised of any further
                            developments connected with this matter.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>